<!-- This is a standard template for the module overview  -->
<!-- Each Module Should have an overview explaining exactly what it does, and giving an overview of the blocks and hooks that it includes or accepts. -->
<div class="xar-mod-head">
    <span class="xar-mod-title"><xar:mlstring>SIGMA Personnel Administration</xar:mlstring></span>
</div>
<div class="xar-mod-body">
    <img src="modules/adminpanels/xarimages/admin.gif" class="xar-module-icon" alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" />

    <h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>

    <h3><xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring></h3>
    <p>
        <em><xar:mlstring>This module takes care of the data of the SIGMA personnel.</xar:mlstring></em>
        <xar:mlstring>It is currently responsible for accomplishing two main tasks:</xar:mlstring>
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Manage all data of SIGMA Personnel, both personal as educational.</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Manage the presence of these personnel members.</xar:mlstring></li>

    </ol>
    <p><xar:mlstring>This module allows for the following entities to be stored:</xar:mlstring>
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><xar:mlstring>examples of standard Xaraya functions commented in plain terms, and written with Xaraya coding standards.</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring>templates with standard style classes, layouts and template requirements to meet Xaraya Block Layout coding standards.</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring>examples of hooks, blocks, dynamic data properties, and event handlers.</xar:mlstring></li>
    </ul>

    <h3><xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring></h3>
    <p>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Install it first.</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Import the dynamic data descriptions.</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Edit the dynamic parameters so all have at least one item in them.</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Start entering your personnel and tell them to check their data ;).</xar:mlstring></li>
    </p>

    <h3><xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring></h3>
    <ul>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Latest entry. This shows each users his or her latest entry in the presence database</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Presence all. This gives an overview of the presence of you personnel at this moment.</xar:mlstring></li>
    </ul>

    <h3><xar:mlstring>Included Hooks</xar:mlstring></h3>
    <ul>
        <li><xar:mlstring>usermenu -- Allows interface with the "My Account Page"</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring>search -- Allows interface with Search Module</xar:mlstring></li>
    </ul>
    <h3><xar:mlstring>Included Dynamic Data Properties</xar:mlstring></h3>
    <ul>
        <li><xar:mlstring>None</xar:mlstring></li>

    </ul>

    <h3>
        <xar:mlstring>Further Information</xar:mlstring>
    </h3>
    <p>
        <xar:mlstring>Further information on the SIGMA Personnel module can be found at</xar:mlstring>
    </p>
       <ul>
              <li><xar:mlstring>Extension page at</xar:mlstring> <a title="#xarML('SIGMA Personnel Module - Xaraya Extension 418')#" href="http://www.xaraya.com/index.php/release/418.html">Xaraya Extension and Releases</a>.
              <xar:mlstring> Click on Version History tab at the bottom to get the latest release information.</xar:mlstring>
              </li>
              <li><xar:mlstring>Related tutorials and documentation can be found at</xar:mlstring> <a href="http://www.sigmautrecht.nl/" title="#xarML('Related documentation on Example')#"><xar:mlstring>Xaraya Documentation.</xar:mlstring></a>
              </li>
         </ul>
         <p class="xar-sub">
             <strong>&nbsp;<xar:mlstring>SIGMA Personnel Module - Overview</xar:mlstring></strong><br />&nbsp;<xar:mlstring>Version</xar:mlstring> 1.0.0&nbsp; 2005-11-13
         </p>
      </div>
</div>
